moderate Reverse Tabnapping

  • Module: swagger-ui
  • Published: June 17th 2019
  • Reported by: Unknown
  • CWE-1022
  • Vulnerable: <3.18.0
  • Patched: >=3.18.0
  • CVSS: 3

Overview

Versions of swagger-ui prior to 3.18.0 are vulnerable to Reverse Tabnapping. The package uses target='_blank' in anchor tags, allowing attackers to access window.opener for the original page. This is commonly used for phishing attacks.

Findings

  • swagger-ui

Remediation

Upgrade to version 3.18.0 or later.

References

  • Swagger-UI Release
  • Snyk Report

More about this vulnerability

moderate Cross-Site Scripting

  • Module: swagger-ui
  • Published: June 17th 2019
  • Reported by: Unknown
  • CWE-79
  • Vulnerable: <3.20.9
  • Patched: >=3.20.9
  • CVSS: 6

Overview

Versions of swagger-ui prior to 3.20.9 are vulnerable to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS). The package fails to sanitize URLs used in the OAuth auth flow, which may allow attackers to execute arbitrary JavaScript.

Findings

  • swagger-ui

Remediation

Upgrade to version 3.20.9 or later.

References

  • GitHub PR
  • Snyk Report

More about this vulnerability

moderate Cross-Site Scripting

  • Module: swagger-ui
  • Published: June 18th 2019
  • Reported by: webron
  • CWE-79
  • Vulnerable: <3.0.13
  • Patched: >=3.0.13
  • CVSS: 5

Overview

Versions of swagger-ui prior to 3.0.13 are vulnerable to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS). The package fails to sanitize YAML files imported from URLs or copied-pasted. This may allow attackers to execute arbitrary JavaScript.

Findings

  • swagger-ui

Remediation

Upgrade to version 3.0.13 or later.

References

  • GitHub Issue
  • Snyk Report

More about this vulnerability

high Prototype Pollution

  • Module: set-value
  • Published: June 20th 2019
  • Reported by: Jon Schlinkert
  • CWE-471
  • CVE-2019-10747
  • Vulnerable: <2.0.1 || >=3.0.0 <3.0.1
  • Patched: >=2.0.1 <3.0.0 || >=3.0.1
  • CVSS: 5

Overview

Versions of set-value prior to 3.0.1 or 2.0.1 are vulnerable to Prototype Pollution. The set function fails to validate which Object properties it updates. This allows attackers to modify the prototype of Object, causing the addition or modification of an existing property on all objects.

Remediation

If you are using set-value 3.x, upgrade to version 3.0.1 or later. If you are using set-value 2.x, upgrade to version 2.0.1 or later.

References

  • Snyk Report

More about this vulnerability

high Prototype Pollution

  • Module: mixin-deep
  • Published: June 20th 2019
  • Reported by: Snyk Security Team
  • CWE-471
  • CVE-2019-10746
  • Vulnerable: <1.3.2 || >=2.0.0 <2.0.1
  • Patched: >=1.3.2 <2.0.0 || >=2.0.1
  • CVSS: 5

Overview

Versions of mixin-deep prior to 2.0.1 or 1.3.2 are vulnerable to Prototype Pollution. The mixinDeep function fails to validate which Object properties it updates. This allows attackers to modify the prototype of Object, causing the addition or modification of an existing property on all objects.

Remediation

If you are using mixin-deep 2.x, upgrade to version 2.0.1 or later. If you are using mixin-deep 1.x, upgrade to version 1.3.2 or later.

References

  • Snyk Report

More about this vulnerability

high Prototype Pollution

  • Module: lodash
  • Published: July 15th 2019
  • Reported by: Snyk Security Team
  • CWE-471
  • CVE-2019-10744
  • Vulnerable: <4.17.12
  • Patched: >=4.17.12
  • CVSS: 3

Overview

Versions of lodash before 4.17.12 are vulnerable to Prototype Pollution. The function defaultsDeep allows a malicious user to modify the prototype of Object via {constructor: {prototype: {...}}} causing the addition or modification of an existing property that will exist on all objects.

high Prototype Pollution

  • Module: handlebars
  • Published: September 16th 2019
  • Reported by: itszn
  • CWE-471
  • Vulnerable: <4.3.0
  • Patched: >=4.3.0
  • CVSS: 6

Overview

Versions of handlebars prior to are vulnerable to Prototype Pollution leading to Remote Code Execution. Templates may alter an Objects' __proto__ and __defineGetter__ properties, which may allow an attacker to execute arbitrary code through crafted payloads.

Findings

  • jest>jest-cli>@jest/core>@jest/reporters>istanbul-reports>handlebars

Remediation

Upgrade to version 4.3.0 or later.

More about this vulnerability

critical Cryptographically Weak PRNG

  • Module: generator-jhipster
  • Published: September 26th 2019
  • Reported by: Jonathan Leitschuh
  • CWE-338
  • CVE-2019-16303
  • Vulnerable: <6.3.0
  • Patched: >=6.3.0
  • CVSS: 3

Overview

Versions of generator-jhipster use a Cryptographically Weak PRNG that may lead to account takeover. The package uses a cryptographically insecure method to generate password reset links, which allows an attacker to guess password reset links and takeover accounts.

Findings

  • generator-jhipster

Remediation

Update to version 6.3.0 or later.

References

  • GitHub Advisory
  • JHipster Release
  • Snyk Report

More about this vulnerability
